=Love is Always Online=

32
00:01:31,020 --> 00:01:33,940
=Episode 20=

33
00:01:41,060 --> 00:01:42,080
My aunt?

34
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,100
Yeah.

35
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:46,040
Jianing and I ran into her
while having a meal.

36
00:01:47,340 --> 00:01:48,720
Did she give you a hard time?

37
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:51,040
No, she even paid for the meal.

38
00:01:51,290 --> 00:01:52,250
That's good to hear.

39
00:01:53,860 --> 00:01:55,700
You shouldn't drink too much coffee.

40
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:56,800
Two cups max.

41
00:01:57,260 --> 00:01:58,760
I'm watching you all the while.

42
00:01:59,260 --> 00:02:00,420
You're a big boss.

43
00:02:00,420 --> 00:02:02,080
Why keep an eye on your staff?

44
00:02:05,140 --> 00:02:06,520
Dear, you're wronging me.

45
00:02:06,980 --> 00:02:09,160
I'm only watching you, not anyone else.

46
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:10,970
I'm off now.

47
00:02:10,970 --> 00:02:11,830
Bye.

48
00:02:20,860 --> 00:02:22,760
Turn the data inside into files.

49
00:02:22,900 --> 00:02:24,120
Get it to me in two hours.

50
00:02:25,740 --> 00:02:27,000
Two hours?

51
00:02:27,260 --> 00:02:29,000
That's too much to be done in two hours.

52
00:02:30,500 --> 00:02:32,420
To work at Ruishi,

53
00:02:32,420 --> 00:02:34,280
you need to be good at multitasking.

54
00:02:36,620 --> 00:02:38,060
The boss values you,

55
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,640
but it doesn't mean you can slack off.

56
00:02:41,260 --> 00:02:42,680
Everyone here works hard.

57
00:02:42,980 --> 00:02:44,600
Don't you have an assistant?

58
00:02:45,580 --> 00:02:47,880
No problem.
I'll give it to you in two hours.

59
00:02:48,540 --> 00:02:49,480
Alright.

60
00:02:53,780 --> 00:02:54,720
Yao.

61
00:02:55,260 --> 00:02:57,400
I'll tell the master about this later.

62
00:02:58,300 --> 00:02:59,440
I don't want others to think

63
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:01,140
I'm getting special treatment.

64
00:03:05,260 --> 00:03:07,080
That's actually the unfair treatment.

65
00:03:07,420 --> 00:03:08,640
I'll talk to Anlan...

66
00:03:09,260 --> 00:03:10,200
Just focus on your work.

67
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:11,840
I'll handle it.

68
00:03:20,620 --> 00:03:21,560
Did you hear?

69
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:23,220
Ms. Wang went after Yao Yuan.

70
00:03:23,220 --> 00:03:24,340
- Really?
- Yeah.

71
00:03:24,340 --> 00:03:25,580
She's so close to the boss.

72
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:26,920
Surely, she should be targeted.

73
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:29,520
What if she is indeed dating the boss?

74
00:03:29,660 --> 00:03:30,940
That's impossible.

75
00:03:30,940 --> 00:03:32,960
She's so skinny and plain.

76
00:03:33,350 --> 00:03:34,380
Maybe the boss just

77
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:36,800
likes her vulnerable, helpless look.

78
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:38,800
Yao Yuan,

79
00:03:39,660 --> 00:03:40,880
have you noticed that the boss

80
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:42,500
often stares at you?

81
00:03:43,260 --> 00:03:44,220
Really?

82
00:03:44,220 --> 00:03:45,380
I've never felt that.

83
00:03:45,380 --> 00:03:46,340
It happens all the time.

84
00:03:46,340 --> 00:03:48,060
Even the others have noticed.

85
00:03:48,060 --> 00:03:49,640
Maybe you just haven't realized it.

86
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:52,300
Or is this your way

87
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:53,700
to move around to catch

88
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:55,840
the boss's eye?

89
00:03:59,860 --> 00:04:01,160
We're really curious.

90
00:04:01,380 --> 00:04:03,280
How did you and the boss meet?

91
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:05,460
He made coffee for you

92
00:04:05,460 --> 00:04:07,040
and told you not to overwork yourself.

93
00:04:07,260 --> 00:04:08,560
Why not teach us a few tricks?

94
00:04:12,860 --> 00:04:14,800
I never asked the boss to look after me.

95
00:04:15,260 --> 00:04:17,520
Nor did I expect any extra attention
from him.

96
00:04:19,180 --> 00:04:21,100
If all your energy goes into that,

97
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:22,160
I'd say you might as well

98
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:23,860
focus more on your work.

99
00:04:25,420 --> 00:04:27,380
Mrs. Jiang's side is coming out.

100
00:04:27,380 --> 00:04:28,660
Your true colors are showing.

101
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:30,040
I didn't mean it like that.

102
00:04:30,260 --> 00:04:31,360
What's all the noise about?

103
00:04:33,580 --> 00:04:35,680
Even making coffee turns into a fuss?

104
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:40,240
Are you done yet?

105
00:04:41,140 --> 00:04:42,520
I've sent it to your email.

106
00:04:43,780 --> 00:04:44,720
Alright then.

107
00:04:45,060 --> 00:04:47,400
Get ten picture frames
from the warehouse.

108
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:49,120
Deliver them to this address.

109
00:04:52,980 --> 00:04:55,520
I hope you'll deliver them yourself.

110
00:04:55,940 --> 00:04:57,480
Taxi fare will be reimbursed.

111
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:23,880
The easel is right up there.

112
00:05:24,380 --> 00:05:25,320
Okay, thanks.

113
00:05:35,340 --> 00:05:36,280
Are you okay?

114
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:38,960
Why would the company send a woman

115
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:40,660
for such heavy work? Let me help you.

116
00:05:40,660 --> 00:05:41,640
It's fine; I got this.

117
00:05:42,660 --> 00:05:43,600
Thank you.

118
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:46,980
Here, got it.

119
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:47,920
Thanks.

120
00:05:54,140 --> 00:06:00,020
(Ruishi Investment Advisory)

121
00:06:26,820 --> 00:06:27,880
Where are you...?

122
00:06:28,180 --> 00:06:29,680
I'm heading to the 24th floor, too.

123
00:06:30,260 --> 00:06:31,700
Do you work at Ruishi?

124
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:32,640
Yes.

125
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:34,300
Ruishi is a great company.

126
00:06:34,300 --> 00:06:35,840
My son works there, too.

127
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:37,640
I'm here to bring him some snacks.

128
00:06:41,820 --> 00:06:42,960
What's wrong with the light?

129
00:06:44,260 --> 00:06:45,800
Could the elevator be broken?

130
00:06:46,540 --> 00:06:47,940
Maybe not.

131
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:49,440
It's probably just a light that's out.

132
00:06:52,180 --> 00:06:53,500
The elevator really broke down.

133
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:54,680
What should we do now?

134
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:56,520
Please don't panic.

135
00:07:00,300 --> 00:07:02,020
Hello, the elevator is malfunctioning.

136
00:07:02,020 --> 00:07:03,800
Is there anyone who can fix it?

137
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:05,740
There was a power outage.

138
00:07:05,740 --> 00:07:07,660
We've contacted the maintenance center.

139
00:07:07,660 --> 00:07:08,900
They'll handle it asap.

140
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:11,120
Please be patient and try to stay calm.

141
00:07:13,020 --> 00:07:15,900
This elevator's like an empty box
hanging in midair.

142
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:17,640
If it breaks, it's really dangerous.

143
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:20,680
Don't panic.

144
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:21,960
They've gone to check it out.

145
00:07:22,140 --> 00:07:23,380
It should be fixed soon.

146
00:07:23,380 --> 00:07:24,540
Let's not scare ourselves.

147
00:07:24,540 --> 00:07:25,480
- Stay calm.
- Okay.

148
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:28,920
What should we do now?

149
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:31,800
Ma'am, give me your hand.

150
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:33,160
Let's lean against the wall.

151
00:07:33,300 --> 00:07:34,600
Bend your knees slightly.

152
00:07:36,580 --> 00:07:37,560
Thank you.

153
00:07:37,860 --> 00:07:39,040
Luckily, you're here.

154
00:07:44,700 --> 00:07:46,160
There is no signal.

155
00:07:48,060 --> 00:07:49,560
Do you want to call the hospital?

156
00:07:50,940 --> 00:07:53,120
No, I want to call my boyfriend.

157
00:07:53,540 --> 00:07:56,120
Hearing his voice
will help me stay calm.

158
00:07:56,820 --> 00:07:58,690
You do love your boyfriend a lot.

159
00:08:06,940 --> 00:08:08,200
Thank goodness.

160
00:08:16,260 --> 00:08:17,200
It's okay now.

161
00:08:18,020 --> 00:08:19,340
Amitabha.

162
00:08:19,340 --> 00:08:20,280
Thank you.

163
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,780
No problem. I'll leave you to it then.

164
00:08:22,780 --> 00:08:24,360
I'll get back to work.

165
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:30,920
How nice for Anlan to have
such a great employee.

166
00:08:36,260 --> 00:08:37,200
Mom.

167
00:08:38,940 --> 00:08:40,000
Why are you here?

168
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,580
I just heard someone got stuck
in the elevator.

169
00:08:42,580 --> 00:08:43,620
Are you okay?

170
00:08:43,620 --> 00:08:44,470
Look.

171
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:45,580
I'm fine.

172
00:08:46,460 --> 00:08:48,880
I brought the snacks you like.

173
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:53,920
I heard from your aunt

174
00:08:55,420 --> 00:08:57,760
that she saw Jianing with her friend.

175
00:08:58,180 --> 00:09:00,600
Is that girl your girlfriend?

176
00:09:01,860 --> 00:09:02,800
Mom,

177
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:05,120
did you come just for that?

178
00:09:05,660 --> 00:09:06,840
Of course.

179
00:09:08,180 --> 00:09:10,880
Why didn't you tell me
about your girlfriend?

180
00:09:11,260 --> 00:09:12,840
You didn't even bring her to meet me.

181
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:16,000
Which lady is she?

182
00:09:17,170 --> 00:09:18,060
I was planning

183
00:09:18,060 --> 00:09:20,400
to introduce her to you properly.

184
00:09:21,140 --> 00:09:24,320
We're family,
no need for that formality.

185
00:09:27,260 --> 00:09:28,200
Alright.

186
00:09:35,820 --> 00:09:36,760
Yao Yuan.

187
00:09:37,220 --> 00:09:38,560
Come to my office.

188
00:09:42,060 --> 00:09:43,260
Mom, you can see for yourself.

189
00:09:44,770 --> 00:09:46,250
Why keep it all so secretive?

190
00:09:50,460 --> 00:09:51,400
It's you.

191
00:09:52,460 --> 00:09:53,400
Ma'am.

192
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:56,520
You know each other?

193
00:09:58,020 --> 00:09:59,220
We were stuck together

194
00:09:59,220 --> 00:10:00,880
in the elevator just now.

195
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,800
You were stuck in the elevator?

196
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:04,460
Let me see if you're hurt.

197
00:10:04,460 --> 00:10:06,180
- I'm fine.
- Let me check.

198
00:10:06,180 --> 00:10:07,200
It's nothing.

199
00:10:08,060 --> 00:10:09,200
What happened to your hand?

200
00:10:09,380 --> 00:10:10,320
It's nothing.

201
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:14,740
Mom.

202
00:10:14,740 --> 00:10:16,020
This is Yao Yuan, my boyfriend.

203
00:10:19,540 --> 00:10:21,280
Oh, you're Anlan's mom.

204
00:10:21,740 --> 00:10:23,800
Hello, I'm Yao Yuan.

205
00:10:26,380 --> 00:10:28,640
Thanks to Miss Yao just now.

206
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:30,480
If I got stuck

207
00:10:30,740 --> 00:10:31,960
in the elevator alone,

208
00:10:32,140 --> 00:10:33,200
I didn't know...

209
00:10:34,220 --> 00:10:35,380
Thank you.

210
00:10:35,380 --> 00:10:37,400
No problem, it's okay.

211
00:10:42,540 --> 00:10:44,120
Well, you two get back to work.

212
00:10:45,140 --> 00:10:47,340
Anlan, come home for dinner tonight.

213
00:10:47,340 --> 00:10:48,680
Your dad will be home.

214
00:10:48,820 --> 00:10:50,760
Your grandparents miss you a lot.

215
00:10:52,260 --> 00:10:53,200
Okay.

216
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:54,680
I'll head out first.

217
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:56,260
Bye, Mom.

218
00:10:56,260 --> 00:10:57,200
Bye.

219
00:10:59,340 --> 00:11:00,580
Not bad.

220
00:11:00,580 --> 00:11:02,000
I was so scared.

221
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:04,920
Impressive.

222
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:07,800
I'm dressed like this.

223
00:11:19,140 --> 00:11:20,240
How did you get hurt?

224
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:23,120
I hurt myself moving some things.

225
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,800
Who told you to move stuff?

226
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:28,160
Other people can do that.

227
00:11:29,580 --> 00:11:31,480
I wanted to help out myself.

228
00:11:33,820 --> 00:11:35,060
You know how I am.

229
00:11:35,060 --> 00:11:36,640
I don't want to rely on others.

230
00:11:37,540 --> 00:11:39,420
It's just a scratch.
Don't worry about it.

231
00:11:39,420 --> 00:11:40,480
Don't bother with it.

232
00:11:47,380 --> 00:11:48,320
Promise me

233
00:11:48,820 --> 00:11:49,880
to take care of yourself.

234
00:11:50,620 --> 00:11:51,640
Don't get hurt, okay?

235
00:11:53,260 --> 00:11:54,440
I know.

236
00:11:55,940 --> 00:11:56,880
I'm sorry.

237
00:11:57,540 --> 00:11:58,640
I can't take you home

238
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:00,760
today.

239
00:12:02,340 --> 00:12:03,280
It's okay.

240
00:12:03,420 --> 00:12:05,020
Spending time with family is important.

241
00:12:07,180 --> 00:12:08,320
I'll find a time soon

242
00:12:09,180 --> 00:12:10,800
to formally introduce you to my family.

243
00:12:13,620 --> 00:12:14,560
Sure.

244
00:12:14,820 --> 00:12:15,760
Does it still hurt?

245
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:17,440
Yeah, it does.

246
00:12:20,660 --> 00:12:21,740
Anlan.

247
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:22,680
Grandma.

248
00:12:22,860 --> 00:12:23,700
Have a seat.

249
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:26,200
What brought you back this time?

250
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:29,320
Home is where you always belong.

251
00:12:29,620 --> 00:12:30,900
You should come back more often.

252
00:12:31,100 --> 00:12:32,440
Okay, Grandpa.

253
00:12:40,420 --> 00:12:41,360
Dad.

254
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:46,440
Dad.

255
00:12:46,580 --> 00:12:47,520
Mom.

256
00:12:47,820 --> 00:12:48,840
Have a seat.

257
00:12:50,660 --> 00:12:51,600
Sit down.

258
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:55,880
Come on.

259
00:12:56,340 --> 00:12:57,360
Everyone, dig in.

260
00:12:59,220 --> 00:13:00,220
Anlan.

261
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:02,020
There are lots of dishes you like today.

262
00:13:02,020 --> 00:13:03,160
Eat more.

263
00:13:04,180 --> 00:13:05,720
Thanks, Mom. You eat more, too.

264
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:07,660
Anlan,

265
00:13:07,660 --> 00:13:09,080
what have you been busy with lately?

266
00:13:09,340 --> 00:13:10,580
We only get to see you

267
00:13:10,580 --> 00:13:11,640
at family gatherings.

268
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:14,360
Are you busy spending time
with your girlfriend?

269
00:13:21,220 --> 00:13:22,360
Do you have a girlfriend now?

270
00:13:24,020 --> 00:13:25,300
Why haven't you brought her back?

271
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:29,080
What reservations do you have
about introducing her?

272
00:13:31,780 --> 00:13:33,080
I'll find some time

273
00:13:33,420 --> 00:13:35,840
to bring her back
and formally introduce her to everyone.

274
00:13:37,140 --> 00:13:38,300
The kid's grown up now

275
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:39,880
and has his own opinions.

276
00:13:40,340 --> 00:13:41,860
But in matters like this,

277
00:13:41,860 --> 00:13:44,600
he has to make the final call himself.

278
00:13:47,420 --> 00:13:48,920
Then let's do it on my birthday.

279
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:50,240
Anlan,

280
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,520
bring your girlfriend over that day,

281
00:13:52,780 --> 00:13:54,180
so your grandparents can meet her.

282
00:13:55,820 --> 00:13:56,760
Alright.

283
00:13:58,220 --> 00:13:59,160
Dad,

284
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:01,160
there's a project budget...

285
00:14:01,380 --> 00:14:03,200
It's rare for us
to have dinner together.

286
00:14:04,420 --> 00:14:05,880
No business talk at the table.

287
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:10,960
We just focus on Anlan's love life.

